On this anniversary of September 11, we pause to reflect on that horrific day 24 years ago. We honor the fallen, the brave first responders, and the countless lives forever changed. In America’s darkest hour, we came together. Strangers embraced, neighbors helped one another, and our nation showed resilience on the world stage. Today, may we honor those who faced evil with courage and remember their sacrifice. We will never forget. 🇺🇸

I am devastated to hear of the passing of Charlie Kirk. He was a bold voice for faith and freedom who loved God, his family, and his country fiercely. Minutes before his passing, he encouraged students at Utah Valley University to pursue a relationship with Christ. May God comfort his family and friends in the days and months to come.
Please join me in praying for Charlie Kirk.

Guardian Bikes in Seymour is reshoring manufacturing and leading the way in American innovation thanks to President Trump’s pro-growth policies. Their story is a true example of entrepreneurship and perseverance. I’m proud to have @guardianbikes growing and thriving here in Indiana’s Ninth District. 🇺🇸

Last night, Guardian Bikes hosted Supply Chain Independence Day to celebrate their new U.S. frame manufacturing facility in Seymour. I joined CEO Brian Riley, Mark Cuban, and trade attorney Charles Benoit for a panel on tariffs, onshoring, and bringing jobs back to America.

President Trump’s plan to rebuild the greatest economy in the world is working. For too long, our workers and industries were undercut by unfair foreign subsidies. Now, we are rebalancing trade agreements so American manufacturers can finally compete on a level playing field. In communities like Seymour, that means plants can stay open and expand production. It also means more local jobs instead of opportunities moving overseas.

It was a great event. Thank you to @guardianbikes for hosting and celebrating American manufacturing! 🇺🇸

Last year, I had the honor of meeting Jason and Mandy Hughes after the passing of their son, Carson, whose beautiful artwork won the Congressional Art Competition was displayed in the U.S. Capitol. They shared with me a #BeLikeCarson bracelet, and I’ve worn it every day since.

This week, I was deeply humbled to return Carson’s winning photo, “Breakfast Time”, to Jason and Mandy along with a book of the many places I carried Carson’s spirit with me over the past year. It has been a daily reminder of Carson’s faith, light, creativity, positive outlook and the impact he continues to have. Though I never knew Carson, I feel l know a little more of him and the blessing he was to so many through Jason and Mandy.

📡 Introducing the Data BRIDGE Act. This bipartisan bill will bring high-speed broadband to the fields that feed America. Too often, cropland and pastures are left off the FCC’s broadband map, cutting farmers off from the precision ag technology they need to boost yields, cut costs, and stay competitive. This bill makes sure federal broadband dollars reach the acres where the work happens.

Excited to announce that over $14 million in Community Project Funding for Indiana’s 9th District is moving forward in the House Appropriations process.

Each year, local governments can submit requests for Community Project Funding through our office, giving communities the opportunity to secure federal support for important local projects.

I’m pleased that all nine of our requests, submitted on behalf of Southern Indiana communities, have been advanced by the House Appropriations Committee. These requests can make local projects a reality, and I’m proud to support them.
Thank you for having me!
